IN the INTEREST OF: O.S.F. ED 105835 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION FIVE. Filed: May 9, 2018 Christopher M. Braeske, 8008 Carondelet Ave., Ste. 300, St. Louis, MO 63105, for appellant. Jennifer C. Hoffman, 105 S. Central Avenue, Clayton, MO 63105, Richard J. Childress, 111 North 7 th Street, Suite 329, St. Louis, MO 63101, for respondents. William P. Grant, 7733 Forsyth Blvd., Ste. 1850, St. Louis, MO 63105, Guardian Ad Litem. Before James M. Dowd, C.J., Lawrence E. Mooney, J., and Jason M. Sengheiser, Sp.J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM.

Mother, B.K., challenges the judgment of the Circuit Court of St. Louis County terminating her parental rights to the child, O.S.F., who was 5 years old at the time of trial and judgment. 1 Finding no error, we affirm.

An opinion would have no precedential value. We have provided the parties with a memorandum, for their information only, setting forth the reasons for this decision.

We affirm the trial court's judgment. Rule 84.16(b)(1).

The court also terminated the rights of the child's father, but his rights are not at issue in this appeal.
